{"title":"Cascada’s Warm Weather All-Road Apparel","link":"https://theradavist.com/cascadas-warm-weather-all-road-apparel/","date":1715352612000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2818\" height=\"1879\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?fit=1200,1879&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?w=2818&amp;quality=75 2818w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Cascada_All-Road-Apparel.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>With warmer weather on the way, apparel company Cascada has a full run of lightweight jerseys, cargo bibs, and baselayers in its new summer drop. All of Cascada’s apparel is made in Italy, and these new jerseys feature micro-perforations to keep you cool on the hottest of days. The new cargo bibs feature an OEKO-tex chamois, cargo pockets, and an all-new abrasion-resistant material on the legs.</p>\n<p>Check out the full drop at <a href=\"https://cascada.cc/en-us/collections/cycling-jerseys-and-cargo-bibs\" target=\"_blank\">Cascada</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/cascadas-warm-weather-all-road-apparel/\">Cascada’s Warm Weather All-Road Apparel</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"a059dd2a7919534312a83685f4cb6b70375afb7c4f49ff281f376f460e98ea3b","category":"Cycling"